President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation ordering the flag of the United States to be flown at half-staff in honor of the victims of the shooting at Marjory Stoneman Douglas High School in Parkland, Florida. The order applies to the White House, public buildings, military posts, naval stations, naval vessels, and all United States embassies and facilities abroad. The flag will be flown at half-staff until sunset on February 19, 2018.